  <title>Preliminaries</title>
  <metadata>
  <md:content-id>m31815</md:content-id><md:title>Preliminaries</md:title>
  <md:abstract>The module provides a review of the background concepts needed for the study of analog and digital communications: the Fourier transform, various definitions of bandwith, the Dirac delta, frequency-domain representation of sinusoids, frequency-domain plotting in Matlab, linear time invariant (LTI) systems, linear filtering, lowpass filters, and Matlab design of lowpass filters.</md:abstract>
